The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has warned internet fraudsters popularly known as ‘Yahoo Boys’ in Nigeria that going diabolical by using charms will not stop its operatives from arresting them. The anti-graft agency disclosed this via a post on its Facebook page on Wednesday, urging the fraudsters to either give in or give up. The statement reads, “No going back on the onslaught against yahoo-yahoo or yahoo-plus, whatever nomenclature. Give up, or give in. The Eagle will get you anytime, anywhere! #Eagleseries57 #EFCC #stopyahooyahoonow. Nigerians React To Viral Video Of Teenagers Begging To Learn… Juju: EFCC Arrests Michael Jackson In Lagos “Yahoo boys now going Spiritual. Even doing money Ritual and making it the new Usual. We will come for those individual(s). Tell them, it won’t be business as usual.”